headline: Exclusive: Sen. Warren urges Fed to reconsider removing Wells Fargo asset cap
summary: Senator Elizabeth Warren (D-Ma.) is calling on the Federal Reserve to reverse its decision and reinstall its asset cap placed on major bank Wells Fargo (WFC). The US central bank released Wells Fargo from its cap that held its total assets at $1.95 trillion earlier this week, allowing its business to expand further.
